The Q&A Handbook for Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) on Vietnam's Carbon Market, Toward 2030 is designed to provide foundational knowledge, practical guidance, and support tools to help Vietnamese enterprises proactively participate in the green transition and integrate into domestic and international carbon markets.

The handbook content is presented in a Q&A format, easy to reference, covering six core topic groups:

(1) Concepts and legal frameworks related to carbon credits;

(2) Processes for calculating emissions, designing, and implementing emission reduction projects;

(3) Financial mechanisms, green credit, and economic benefits from carbon credits;

(4) Tools, training, and technical support for enterprises;

(5) Risk management, transparency, and best practices; and

(6) International experience and lessons for Vietnam.

The handbook not only compiles the latest legal regulations (as of 2025) such as Decree 06/2022/Nƒê-CP, Decree 119/2025/Nƒê-CP, and the roadmap for developing the national carbon trading exchange, but also provides specific guidance for SMEs to build MRV (Measurement ‚Äì Reporting ‚Äì Verification) systems, select emission factors, access green capital, and participate in public-private partnership models.

By combining professional knowledge, practical examples, and applicable tools, the handbook aims to help Vietnamese enterprises seize carbon economic opportunities while contributing to the national goal of achieving net zero emissions by 2050.
